<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the SINGLE `sp_portal` row that
    defines the Service Portal (Experience Portal) entry-point of the scoped
    application `x_casemgmt`.

    PURPOSE (AAP Section 0.1.1 / Section 0.4.4 / Section 0.7.2):
      This portal is the ServiceNow target replacement for ArkCase's
      `acm-service-portal-gateway` anonymous-request pattern - specifically the
      `submitRequest(...)` and `getRequestStatus(...)` methods of the
      `PortalRequestService` interface and its `DefaultPluggablePortalRequestService`
      implementation. Per AAP Section 0.4.4 ("UI Design"), it is the UNAUTHENTICATED
      Experience Portal that hosts exactly two pages:
        - x_casemgmt_case_submit (anonymous case submission form)
        - x_casemgmt_case_status (anonymous case status lookup)
      Per AAP Section 0.7.2 ("User Example - Deployment steps", step 3), the
      deployable URL is:
        [instance URL]/x_casemgmt_case_portal
      which is precisely the `<url_suffix>` value declared below.

    THE PORTAL IS THE SHELL, THE PAGES ARE THE CONTENT:
      This file authors ONLY portal-level metadata (URL suffix, theme reference,
      anonymous-access flag, default homepage, login-page redirect target). The
      interactive UI elements (form inputs, lookup field, result panel) live in
      sibling page records under `pages/` and the embedded widget records under
      `widgets/`. The portal record contains NO widget references and NO embedded
      script bodies; it is pure metadata.

    UNAUTHENTICATED ANONYMOUS-ACCESS DESIGN (AAP Section 0.4.4 verbatim:
    "two unauthenticated pages"):
      Three configuration mechanisms work together to make this a true public,
      anonymous portal:

        1. `<public>true</public>` - explicit signal to the platform's
           authorization layer that this portal is exempt from the standard
           authentication challenge.

        2. `<login_page>x_casemgmt_case_submit</login_page>` (and its
           display-value sibling) - OOB ServiceNow portals default to redirecting
           unauthenticated callers to a `/login` page. By setting the login_page
           reference to the SUBMISSION PAGE ITSELF, anonymous users land directly
           on the case-submission form rather than seeing a username/password
           prompt. This is the canonical ServiceNow pattern for fully anonymous
           Service Portals.

        3. `<homepage>x_casemgmt_case_submit</homepage>` (and its display-value
           sibling) - the default page rendered when a caller hits the bare
           portal URL `[instance URL]/x_casemgmt_case_portal`. Because the
           submission page is the most common entry-point in the user journey
           ("I want to submit a case -> I land on the form"), the submission
           page IS the homepage. The status-lookup page (x_casemgmt_case_status)
           is reachable via direct URL `[instance URL]/x_casemgmt_case_portal?id=x_casemgmt_case_status`.

      All three mechanisms are necessary; omitting any one breaks the anonymous-
      access guarantee. (`<public>true</public>` alone is not enough because
      OOB redirects still pull anonymous users to the login page; setting only
      `login_page` is not enough because the platform's authorization layer
      defaults to deny without the public flag.)

    DEFAULT THEME / NO CUSTOM CSS (AAP Section 0.4.4 verbatim: "Visual
    treatment: ServiceNow Experience Portal default theme. No custom CSS,
    no custom branding."):
      The `<theme>` and `<theme_dv>` fields are intentionally left as empty
      self-closing elements. The platform applies its system-default Service
      Portal theme at render time (the OOB `Stock` theme on most PDIs, or
      whatever theme the PDI release ships with). This guarantees:

        - Zero custom CSS is authored or referenced.
        - Zero custom branding is created.
        - The portal does not depend on a specific theme record's stable name
          (e.g., `stock` / `Stock` / `default`) which can vary across PDI
          releases. Leaving the field empty is the only PDI-release-portable
          choice.

      The agent prompt's Phase 5 explicitly authorizes this fallback:
      "If the agent cannot confirm a stable OOB theme name, set `<theme_dv/>`
      and `<theme/>` to empty self-closing elements; the platform uses its
      built-in default theme."

      Similarly, `<icon>`, `<logo>`, `<background_image>`, and
      `<background_color>` are all empty self-closing elements - no custom
      branding artifacts are referenced. Per AAP Section 0.7.2 (Minimal-Change
      Clause), this is the deliberate, scope-compliant choice.

    OUT-OF-SCOPE FIELDS (deliberately empty):
      `<knowledge_base>` - empty. Knowledge-base integration is OUT OF SCOPE
        per AAP Section 0.3.2 ("Document management ... out of scope"). No
        `kb_knowledge` records are referenced.
      `<catalog>` - empty. Service-catalog integration is OUT OF SCOPE per
        AAP Section 0.3.2 (no requirement for ordering catalog items;
        `acm-service-correspondence` and similar were not in the seven
        enumerated capabilities). No `sc_catalog` records are referenced.
      `<quick_start_guide_url>` - empty. No external getting-started URL
        is provided; the portal is self-explanatory with two pages.
      `<kb_categories_visible>false</kb_categories_visible>` - reinforces
        the empty knowledge-base configuration.

    SCOPE BINDING (AAP Sections 0.5.2 and 0.7.2):
      `<sys_scope>` and `<sys_package>` reference the scoped application by
      its actual scope NAME (`x_casemgmt`), not by sys_id. The actual scope
      record's `<name>` is `x_casemgmt` per `../app/sys_scope/x_casemgmt.xml`,
      and `<scope>x_casemgmt</scope>` per `../app/sys_app/x_casemgmt_case_management.xml`.
      ALL sibling XMLs in this scoped application reference the scope by that
      same name (`x_casemgmt`). Update Set re-import resolves cross-references
      by matching the `<sys_scope>` text-node value against the scope record's
      `<name>`/`<source>` fields, so this MUST match the actual sibling-file
      convention to avoid preview errors. This is the same convention applied
      in `../tables/x_casemgmt_case.xml`, `../roles/sys_user_role_x_casemgmt_case_manager.xml`,
      and every other sibling record in this scoped application.

      The `display_value="Case Management"` and `source="x_casemgmt"` attributes
      are descriptive metadata that ServiceNow uses for human-readable display
      on the Update Set preview page; the actual reference resolution uses the
      text-node values.

    CROSS-REFERENCES BY NAME / NO HARDCODED SYS_IDS (AAP Section 0.7.2):
      Every cross-reference is a name lookup against a stable identifier:
        - `<homepage>x_casemgmt_case_submit</homepage>` and its
          `<homepage_dv display_value="Case Submission">x_casemgmt_case_submit</homepage_dv>`
          sibling resolve against the `<id>x_casemgmt_case_submit</id>` field
          of `../portal/pages/sp_page_x_casemgmt_case_submit.xml`.
        - `<login_page>x_casemgmt_case_submit</login_page>` and its
          `<login_page_dv ...>` sibling resolve against the same
          `<id>x_casemgmt_case_submit</id>` field.
        - `<sys_scope>` / `<sys_package>` resolve against the scope record's
          `<name>` field (`x_casemgmt`).

      The ONLY `sys_id` literal in this file is `<sys_id>` itself (THIS
      record's own primary key). It is the deterministic 32-char lowercase
      hex MD5 of `sp_portal_x_casemgmt_case_portal`:
        printf '%s' 'sp_portal_x_casemgmt_case_portal' | md5sum | cut -c1-32
        -> 82079e7877f4f6d09975ab96fc0fa2fa
      Per AAP Section 0.7.2, the no-hardcoded-sys_id rule applies to
      references TO OTHER records, not to a record's own identity primary key.

    NO PII, NO EMAIL (AAP Section 0.7.2):
      The description and short_description below contain ZERO PII (no real
      names, no real email addresses, no real organization names). Email
      notifications are explicitly disabled on the PDI per AAP Section 0.7.2
      Email-disabled constraint - no notification triggers are configured by
      this portal record (notifications are configured at the table/business-rule
      level, not at the portal level, and AAP Section 0.7.2 prohibits
      configuring any of them).

    `casemgmt` SCOPE IDENTIFIER (AAP Section 0.7.1 implicit / Section 0.7.2):
      All `x_casemgmt_*` references use the concrete scope identifier `casemgmt` per AAP
      Section 0.7.2 ("Scoped-namespace-only constraint"). ServiceNow Update Set
      imports use a standard XML parser, so the scope id is concrete in the XML
      before export. The same identifier is used consistently across every
      sibling XML in this scoped application.

    URL-SUFFIX UNIQUENESS (ServiceNow platform constraint):
      `<url_suffix>` has a primary-key constraint on the `sp_portal` table
      (the platform forbids two portals on the same instance from sharing
      the same suffix). The scope-prefixed value `x_casemgmt_case_portal`
      ensures global uniqueness even with other scoped portals on the same
      PDI. The literal `casemgmt` placeholder is replaced by the actual scope
      id at PDI assignment time, so the final URL on a real instance becomes
      `https://devXXXXXX.service-now.com/x_<actual_scope>_case_portal`.

    XML CONVENTIONS HONORED (matching sibling files in this app):
      - Wrapper element: `<record_update table="sp_portal">` per the agent
        prompt's Phase 1 specification, matching the sibling pattern used
        by `../tables/x_casemgmt_case.xml` and other primary-record XMLs.
      - Indentation: 4 spaces for record fields (matching sibling-file
        convention).
      - Element ordering: alphabetical within the record (matching
        sibling-file convention).
      - sys_scope text-node value: `x_casemgmt` (NOT
        `x_casemgmt_case_management`). The actual scope record's `<name>`
        is `x_casemgmt` per ../app/sys_scope/x_casemgmt.xml, matching every
        sibling XML in this scoped app.
      - sys_package text-node value: `x_casemgmt` with `source="x_casemgmt"`
        attribute, matching the sys_app record's `<scope>x_casemgmt</scope>`
        per ../app/sys_app/x_casemgmt_case_management.xml.
      - Deterministic 32-char lowercase hex sys_id: computed as
        MD5("sp_portal_x_casemgmt_case_portal") = 82079e7877f4f6d09975ab96fc0fa2fa.
        Re-generation of this XML is byte-identical (no random UUIDs).
      - Audit fields: `<sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by>` and
        `<sys_created_on>2025-01-01 00:00:00</sys_created_on>` for stable
        repeatable timestamps (the same date is used by EVERY sibling
        record in this scoped app for repeatable XML re-generation).
      - No smart quotes, no leading/trailing whitespace, no BOM. Strict
        XML conformance for ServiceNow Update Set re-import preview
        (AAP Section 0.7.3 validation gate 7).

    SOURCE-SIDE SEMANTIC REFERENCE (read-only context, NOT byte-for-byte
    ported per AAP Section 0.5.1):

      acm-services/acm-service-portal-gateway/src/main/java/com/armedia/acm/
      portalgateway/service/PortalRequestService.java
        line 39 - public interface PortalRequestService { ... }
        line 52 - PortalResponse submitRequest(String portalId, String
                  externalUserId, PortalRequest request) throws
                  PortalRequestServiceException;
        line 71-72 - PortalResponse getRequestStatus(String portalId, String
                     portalUserId, String requestType, String requestId)
                     throws PortalRequestServiceException;

      acm-services/acm-service-portal-gateway/src/main/java/com/armedia/acm/
      portalgateway/service/DefaultPluggablePortalRequestService.java
        line 48 - public class DefaultPluggablePortalRequestService implements
                  PortalRequestService { ... }
        line 60-65 - submitRequest(...) implementation; resolves provider by
                     request type and forwards.
        line 86-92 - getRequestStatus(...) implementation; resolves provider
                     by request type and forwards.

      ArkCase implements anonymous portal access through a Java Spring service
      that resolves a `PortalRequestServiceProvider` bean by request type
      (e.g., FOIA) and forwards the call. The ServiceNow target eliminates
      the Spring bean indirection entirely:
        - The "anonymous-submit" semantic (PortalRequestService.submitRequest)
          maps to the SUBMIT scripted REST endpoint backing the
          x_casemgmt_case_submit page (authored in the sibling
          `../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_casemgmt_case_submit.xml`).
        - The "status-lookup" semantic (PortalRequestService.getRequestStatus)
          maps to the LOOKUP scripted REST endpoint backing the
          x_casemgmt_case_status page (authored in the sibling
          `../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_casemgmt_case_status_lookup.xml`).
      THIS portal record does NOT host either scripted REST endpoint - it
      hosts the PAGES that invoke them. The two scripted REST endpoints are
      separate records in `../portal/rest/`, and the page widgets in
      `../portal/widgets/` make the HTTP calls to them.

    CROSS-REFERENCES (AAP Section 0.5.2 dependency ordering):
      THIS RECORD MUST LOAD AFTER:
        - ../app/sys_scope/x_casemgmt.xml (scope record; `<sys_scope>`
          cross-reference resolves against this record's `<name>`)
        - ../app/sys_app/x_casemgmt_case_management.xml (scoped application
          record; `<sys_package>` cross-reference resolves against this
          record's `<scope>`)

      THIS RECORD SHOULD LOAD AFTER (but ServiceNow's two-pass import
      tolerates any order within the same Update Set, since references
      resolve by name):
        - ../portal/pages/sp_page_x_casemgmt_case_submit.xml (homepage
          and login_page references resolve against this page's `<id>`)
        - ../portal/pages/sp_page_x_casemgmt_case_status.xml (the second
          page; reachable via `?id=x_casemgmt_case_status` query parameter
          at runtime)

      THIS RECORD MUST LOAD BEFORE:
        - (none - the portal is the entry-point; no other artifact in
          the scoped application references it. Pages register themselves
          AGAINST this portal via their own `portal` field; the portal
          record itself does not enumerate them.)

    VALIDATION-GATE MAPPING (AAP Section 0.7.3 - the seven validation
    gates):
      This portal record is the FOUNDATIONAL artifact for two of the seven
      validation gates:

        Gate 4 ("Portal - submission"): "Case created from unauthenticated
          portal submission - Case appears in internal list with Draft
          status and correct case number." The portal's `<public>true</public>`
          flag and `<login_page>` redirect-target configuration ensure that
          anonymous users CAN reach the submission page without authentication.
          Without this portal record, the submission page is unreachable to
          anonymous users.

        Gate 5 ("Portal - lookup"): "Status lookup returns correct data for
          valid case number - Correct status/subject/opened_date returned;
          'No case found with that number.' for invalid number." The same
          `<public>true</public>` flag plus the `?id=x_casemgmt_case_status`
          URL convention covers anonymous access to the lookup page.

      Gates 1 (data model), 2 (workflow), 3 (ACLs), 6 (dashboards), and
      7 (Update Set integrity) are not affected by this file.
-->
<record_update table="sp_portal">
    <sp_portal action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <background_color/>
        <background_image/>
        <background_image_dv/>
        <catalog/>
        <catalog_dv/>
        <description>Unauthenticated Experience Portal for the Case Management scoped application. Provides two pages: case_submit (anonymous case submission) and case_status (anonymous case status lookup). Replaces ArkCase's acm-service-portal-gateway anonymous-submission pattern (PortalRequestService.submitRequest and PortalRequestService.getRequestStatus). Per AAP Section 0.4.4 (UI Design - default theme), Section 0.7.2 (deployment step 3 - portal URL), and the seven validation gates (Gate 4 portal-submission, Gate 5 portal-lookup). Public access is enabled via the public flag plus a login_page redirect target that points to the submission page itself, so anonymous callers never see a login prompt. The portal uses the platform default Service Portal theme (no custom CSS, no custom branding) per AAP Section 0.4.4. Knowledge-base and service-catalog integrations are out of scope per AAP Section 0.3.2 and are intentionally empty.</description>
        <enable_legacy_recents>false</enable_legacy_recents>
        <hide_portal_name>false</hide_portal_name>
        <homepage display_value="Case Submission">x_casemgmt_case_submit</homepage>
        <homepage_dv display_value="Case Submission">x_casemgmt_case_submit</homepage_dv>
        <icon/>
        <icon_dv/>
        <kb_categories_visible>false</kb_categories_visible>
        <knowledge_base/>
        <knowledge_base_dv/>
        <login_page display_value="Case Submission">x_casemgmt_case_submit</login_page>
        <login_page_dv display_value="Case Submission">x_casemgmt_case_submit</login_page_dv>
